<P><B>Performance Architect</B></P>
<P>
The Windows Client Platform team is looking for a Performance Architect to help us drive the development of the richest simplest well-performing Windows client side development platform ever. As a Performance Architect, you will have to identify, design and drive the implementation of architectural changes that will improve the overall platform performance. You will have to participate actively on all aspects of our design process to guarantee that performance implications are properly taken into account and that performance plans are appropriate. You will have to work closely with the development team and be willing to make hands-on code changes when appropriate. You will also have to work in close cooperation with our feature and virtual performance teams to drive the development of a well performing product with the right balance between features, schedule and performance. You will have to build high levels of expertise on performance tools, the Common Language Runtime (CLR), the Base Class Library (BCL) and the base OS to act as a technical resource to the team on any performance related issues. You will have to work closely with other performance and project teams around the company to drive Avalon-targeted performance optimizations. As appropriate, you will need to participate on the development of performance tools and performance scenarios. Qualified candidates must have at least 5 years of dedicated hands-on experience on performance work in shipped commercial Windows software
</P>
  


